                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department’s November 10 should be a sufficient response to your November 28,
                    and instruction for your guidance regarding the preferential treatment of
                    European claims and the advisability of sending the circular note.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
